<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14696] DecayingEstimatedHistogramReservoir.EstimatedHistogramReservoirSnapshot returns wrong value for size() and incorrectly calculates count</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14696</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It appears to return the wrong value for no reason. There isn&apos;t a single instance in the code base where we use size. There is an internal count that is calculated, but it is calculated over an empty array. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix both of these bugs and then use the size to only populate read and write latency values used for speculation when there are actual samples being used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
